Conway's Game of Life kata complete. All 8 tests pass:
- empty input → empty output
- single isolated cell dies
- two adjacent cells die
- 2x2 block is stable
- vertical blinker → horizontal blinker
- reproduction (dead cell with 3 neighbors becomes alive)
- overpopulation (live cell with >3 neighbors dies)
- negative coordinates handled correctly

Implementation uses sparse representation via a `Map<CellKey, number>` to count live neighbors of each candidate cell, then applies the survival rule. `experiment-done.txt` written.
